---
import Section from "./Section.astro"
import ContentItem from "./ContentItem.astro"
import { experience, talks } from "../data/site"
---

<Section
  title="About"
  subtitle="Still falling, still learning."
  bordered={false}
>
  <p>
    For years, I've worked as a frontend engineer, building interfaces for
    large-scale projects. I've learned precision, structure, and how to make
    complex systems feel simple.
  </p>
  <p>
    But somewhere along the way, I started craving something more personal —
    something that could reflect not just <i class="text-gray-900">what</i> I do,
    but <i class="text-gray-900">why</i> I do it.
  </p>
  <p>This site is where that idea starts to take form.</p>
  <p>
    It's not a portfolio in the traditional sense. It's a living space — a place
    to experiment, to connect dots between design and engineering, to explore
    the balance between logic and emotion.
  </p>
  <p>
    I'm learning to move slower. To build with intention. To make things that
    last.
  </p>
  <p>This space will grow with me — changing shape as I do.</p>

  <div class="mt-12">
    <h3
      class="mb-6 font-sans text-sm font-medium tracking-wide text-gray-400 uppercase"
    >
      Experience
    </h3>
    <div class="space-y-6">
      {
        experience.map((item) => (
          <ContentItem
            title={item.role}
            subtitle={item.company}
            period={item.period}
            description={item.description}
          />
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-12 border-t border-gray-200 pt-10">
    <h3
      class="mb-6 font-sans text-sm font-medium tracking-wide text-gray-400 uppercase"
    >
      Talks & Writings
    </h3>
    <div class="space-y-6">
      {
        talks.map((item) => (
          <ContentItem
            title={item.title}
            subtitle={item.type}
            period={item.year}
            description={item.description}
            href={item.href}
          />
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>
</Section>
